# NOTE: Comments must be on their own lines — gitignore treats anything
# after the pattern as part of the pattern.

# --- Go binaries ---
# `go build` puts the binary in the package directory by default; CI/local
# builds may use any name. Catch all platforms.
*.exe
*.exe~
*.dll
*.so
*.dylib
sql-go-service
sql-go-service.exe

# --- Go test artifacts ---
# `go test -c` produces a `*.test` binary.
*.test
# Coverage profiles from `go test -coverprofile`.
*.out
coverage.html
coverage.txt

# --- Go workspace files ---
# Per-developer multi-module workspace; not needed for module-mode builds.
go.work
go.work.sum

# --- IDE ---
# Root .gitignore already covers /.vscode globally; this catches IntelliJ/Goland.
.idea/

# --- What we DO commit (FYI for future maintainers) ---
#   go.mod, go.sum         module + dependency lockfile, required for builds
#   cmd/, internal/        all source
#   Dockerfile, scripts/   build + ops
#   testdata/              fixture inputs for tests (Go convention; ALWAYS tracked)
#   *.md                   README, PARITY, POST_MVP, TEST_COVERAGE
